ensive interviews with him, his family, and colleagues. 2019-01-02.\n* [https://achievement.org/achiever/james-d-watson/#interview James D. Watson, Ph.D. Biography and Interview on American Academy of Achievement]\n{{FRS 1981}}\n{{Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine Laureates 1951-1975}}\n{{Winners of the National Medal of Science|biological}}\n{{Copley Medallists 1951\u20132000}}\n{{Eli Lilly Award in Biological Chemistry}}\n{{History of biology}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Watson, James D.}}\n[[Category:James Watson| ]]\n[[Category:1928 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century American physicists]]\n[[Category:20th-century American zoologists]]\n[[Category:21st-century American physicists]]\n[[Category:21st-century American zoologists]]\n[[Category:American atheists]]\n[[Category:American biophysicists]]\n[[Category:American former Christians]]\n[[Category:American geneticists]]\n[[Category:American people of English descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Irish descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Scottish descent]]\n[[Category:American male non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:American science writers]]\n[[Category:American textbook writers]]\n[[Category:Fellows of Clare College, Cambridge]]\n[[Category:Foreign Members of the Royal Society]]\n[[Category:Foreign Members of the Russian Academy of Sciences]]\n[[Category:Foreign Members of the USSR Academy of Sciences]]\n[[Category:Former Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:Guggenheim Fellows]]\n[[Category:Harvard University faculty]]\n[[Category:Hastings Center Fellows]]\n[[Category:Honorary Knights Commander of the Order of the British Empire]]\n[[Category:Indiana University alumni]]\n[[Category:Members of the European Molecular Biology Organization]]\n[[Category:Members of the Royal Irish Academy]]\n[[Category:Members of the United States National Academy of Sciences]]\n[[Category:American molecular biologists]]\n[[Category:National Medal of Science laureates]]\n[[Category:Nobel la